<title>JAPAN: Japan blue-chip stocks rise on bargain-hunting.</title>
<headline>Japan blue-chip stocks rise on bargain-hunting.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-07-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Blue-chip stocks rose early in the Wednesday morning session as investors bargain-hunted the issues which had recently been slipping lower in a correction phase, brokers said.</p>
<p>As of 0032 GMT, Honda Motor Co Ltd shares were up 50 yen at 3,350. Fuji Photo Film rose 20 to 4,500. Optical glass maker Hoya Corp rose 40 to 5,190 while Canon Inc was unchanged at 3,080 yen and Sony Corp was also unchanged at 9,760 yen.</p>
